	<div class="title">
		<strong>Requirements</strong>
	</div>
	<div class="description">
		<h4>Base Requirements</h4>
		<p>If you're not sure if your PHP installation supports these, you can check by either running <a href="http://php.net/phpinfo">phpinfo()</a> in a browser, or running <code>php -i</code> from the command line.</p>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="http://www.php.net/ChangeLog-5.php#5.1.4">PHP 5.1.4</a> or newer; <a href="http://www.php.net/ChangeLog-5.php#5.2.0">PHP 5.2</a> or later is faster.</li>
			<li><a href="http://php.net/curl">cURL</a> 7.15 with OpenSSL (i.e. supports <code>https</code>)</li>
			<li><a href="http://php.net/simplexml">SimpleXML</a></li>
			<li><a href="http://php.net/spl">Standard PHP Library (SPL)</a></li>
		</ul>

		<h4>Caching Requirements</h4>
		<p>Want to be able to leverage response caching? You'll also need one of these sets, depending on the kind of caching you want to use:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="http://php.net/apc">APC</a> extension</li>
			<li><a href="http://xcache.lighttpd.net">XCache</a> extension</li>
			<li><a href="http://php.net/memcache">Memcache</a> extension, with <a href="http://memcached.org">memcached</a></li>
			<li><a href="http://php.net/sqlite3">SQLite 3</a>, <a href="http://php.net/PDO">PDO</a> and the <a href="http://php.net/pdo_sqlite">PDO_SQLITE</a> driver</li>
		</ul>
	</div>

